The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Lever gets new ED
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Lever gets new ED
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Mumbai, July 4: Hindustan Unilever has appointed Hemant Bakshi as the executive director, sales and customer development, with effect from September 1.         
	He will replace Sanjiv Kakkar, who has been appointed Unilever chairman for Russia, Ukraine and Belarus operations, the company said in a filing to the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE). At present, Bakshi is the regional vice-president of South Asia. Unilever shares closed at Rs 201.60, up 2.62 per cent, on the BSE.                                                                                                                                     
